In src/app.css, fix the .row-menu trigger so it is perceivable and operable for keyboard and touch users. Add a selector that reveals the button on keyboard focus, e.g. add `:focus-visible` (and/or `:focus-within` on the row) alongside the existing hover/aria-expanded reveal rule:

.browse-table tbody tr:hover .row-menu-btn,
.browse-table tbody tr:focus-within .row-menu-btn,
.row-menu-btn:focus-visible,
.row-menu-btn[aria-expanded='true'] {
  opacity: 1;
  pointer-events: auto;
}

Also, so touch users can always reach row actions (devices have no :hover), make the button at least faintly visible by default — change the base `.row-menu-btn { opacity: 0; }` to a low but non-zero value such as `opacity: 0.35` (and keep it fully opaque on hover/focus/expanded), OR add a `@media (hover: none)` block that sets `.row-menu-btn { opacity: 1; pointer-events: auto; }`. Finally add a visible focus ring:

.row-menu-btn:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid #6aa6ff;
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

Do not change the DOM structure or the open/close JS logic; only adjust the CSS reveal/focus rules.

In src/app/dom-builders.ts, in the `openMenu(x, y)` function inside makeRowMenu, after setting menu.hidden = false (so it has a measurable size) and before/after setting left/top, clamp the coordinates to the viewport. Read the menu's rendered size and the viewport, e.g.:

const rect = menu.getBoundingClientRect();
const maxX = window.innerWidth - rect.width - 4;
const maxY = window.innerHeight - rect.height - 4;
menu.style.left = Math.max(4, Math.min(x, maxX)) + 'px';
menu.style.top = Math.max(4, Math.min(y, maxY)) + 'px';

Make sure to read getBoundingClientRect() AFTER revealing the menu (menu.hidden = false) so width/height are non-zero. Keep the position:fixed styling and the existing close-on-document-click/Escape behavior unchanged.

In src/app/dom-builders.ts makeRowMenu, dismiss the menu on scroll and resize while it is open. In openMenu, after registering the existing document 'click' and 'keydown' listeners, also register a listener that closes the menu on any scroll (capturing, so it catches scrolls inside the .results overflow container as well as window scroll) and on window resize. E.g. add named handlers:

function onScrollOrResize(): void { closeMenu(); }
window.addEventListener('scroll', onScrollOrResize, true);
window.addEventListener('resize', onScrollOrResize);

and in closeMenu remove them with the same arguments (useCapture=true for scroll):

window.removeEventListener('scroll', onScrollOrResize, true);
window.removeEventListener('resize', onScrollOrResize);

Keep the existing click/Escape behavior and listener teardown unchanged.

In src/app.css, add explicit :focus-visible styling for the row menu trigger and items, matching the app's existing #6aa6ff focus accent. Add:

.row-menu-btn:focus-visible { outline: 2px solid #6aa6ff; outline-offset: 2px; }
.row-menu .btn:focus-visible { outline: 2px solid #6aa6ff; outline-offset: -2px; background: #3a3d41; }

This is additive CSS only; do not remove the existing :hover rules.

